	Ta có $\heva{&BD\parallel \left(\alpha \right)\\&BD\subset \left(SBD\right)\\&\left(SBD\right)\cap \left(\alpha \right)=HK} \Rightarrow HK\parallel BD\Rightarrow \dfrac{SK}{SD}=\dfrac{SH}{SO}=\dfrac{2}{5}$.\\
	Ta có $\dfrac{S_{\triangle SIK}}{S_{\triangle SCD}}=\dfrac{\dfrac{1}{2} SI\cdot SK\cdot \sin S}{\dfrac{1}{2} SC\cdot SD\cdot \sin S}=\dfrac{SI}{SC}\cdot \dfrac{SK}{SD}=\dfrac{1}{4}\cdot \dfrac{2}{5}=\dfrac{1}{10}=0{,}1$.

