methodBlocks.solution:
Ta có $\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sqrt{x+1}-1}{x}=\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\left(\sqrt{x+1}-1\right)\left(\sqrt{x+1}+1\right)}{x\left(\sqrt{x+1}+1\right)}
	=\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{x}{x\left(\sqrt{x+1}+1\right)}
	=\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{x+1}+1}=\dfrac{1}{2}$.

Ta có
	\begin{align*}
		\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sqrt{1+2x}-1}{x}&=\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\left(\sqrt{1+2x}-1\right)\left(\sqrt{1+2x}+1\right)}{x\left(\sqrt{1+2x}+1\right)}
		\\
		&=\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{2x}{x\left(\sqrt{1+2x}+1\right)}
		\\
		&=\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{2}{\sqrt{1+2x}+1}
		\\
		&=1.
	\end{align*}

Chia cả tử và mẫu cho $x$ ta có
	$\lim_{x\to +\infty}\dfrac{2x+1}{x+3}=\lim_{x\to +\infty}
	\dfrac{2+\frac{1}{x}}{1+\frac{3}{x}}= 2$.

